I understand now!

478
00:10:01,160 --> 00:10:03,580
So this is the famous Oden speech!

479
00:10:06,500 --> 00:10:09,510
You came to arrest me?

480
00:10:09,510 --> 00:10:10,300
Yes.

481
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:15,890
But it's not like I want to,
so you could always bribe me...

482
00:10:18,350 --> 00:10:23,100
Now, why would folks stop avoiding me?

483
00:10:23,100 --> 00:10:25,440
A fire has them a little preoccupied.

484
00:10:25,810 --> 00:10:27,610
You mean you don't know, Kin?!

485
00:10:27,940 --> 00:10:29,940
You shouldn't have brought that here!

486
00:10:29,940 --> 00:10:30,820
What?

487
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:32,950
This white boar?

488
00:10:33,320 --> 00:10:39,410
Isn't the Kurokoma boss trying to use it as
bait to destroy the Hyogoro Family?!

489
00:10:39,410 --> 00:10:40,490
What do you mean?!

490
00:10:40,490 --> 00:10:42,910
I mean wherever that little boar is,

491
00:10:42,910 --> 00:10:46,460
its parent will charge in soon after!

492
00:10:51,630 --> 00:10:53,470
Alright!

493
00:11:00,260 --> 00:11:01,810
The boar's parent?

494
00:11:01,810 --> 00:11:05,560
According to an ancient document,
it's a white boar the size of a mountain!

495
00:11:06,060 --> 00:11:08,810
That's why they call it the Mountain God!

496
00:11:08,810 --> 00:11:09,770
What?!

497
00:11:10,270 --> 00:11:14,650
It's said that several centuries ago,
it destroyed a whole region overnight.

498
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:18,320
I thought it was just a myth...

499
00:11:19,120 --> 00:11:20,830
but...

500
00:11:21,160 --> 00:11:25,750
since this white boar exists...

501
00:11:26,290 --> 00:11:29,540
The Mountain God really exists!

502
00:11:29,540 --> 00:11:31,170
It'll eat us alive!

503
00:11:31,170 --> 00:11:33,710
It's already here! Run!

504
00:11:42,260 --> 00:11:44,180
Oh no!

505
00:11:44,180 --> 00:11:46,690
Because of me, the capital's gonna...!

506
00:12:12,460 --> 00:12:13,090
Ko...

507
00:12:17,050 --> 00:12:18,380
– Kozuki Oden!
– Kozuki Oden!

508
00:12:20,340 --> 00:12:23,600
That was quite the story.

509
00:12:23,970 --> 00:12:24,850
– What?
– What?

510
00:12:24,850 --> 00:12:27,350
I do not know who you are...

511
00:12:29,060 --> 00:12:33,190
but surrender that white boar to me!

512
00:12:49,250 --> 00:12:53,130
I can't believe because of this little guy,
the capital is going to be...!

513
00:12:53,130 --> 00:12:55,300
Stop squealing, you!

514
00:12:55,300 --> 00:12:57,840
That is why I told you to give it to me!

515
00:12:57,840 --> 00:12:59,340
No, wait!

516
00:12:59,340 --> 00:13:02,300
This boar is worth one platinum!
That's a lot of money!

517
00:13:02,930 --> 00:13:07,680
Not only can I pay off my debts,
but what remains will be capital for a nest egg!

518
00:13:08,140 --> 00:13:10,190
K-Kozuki Oden!

519
00:13:10,190 --> 00:13:11,400
It's really him!

520
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:17,740
I hate all those dumb grown-ups.
He's the only one I respect!

521
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:27,240
The only time the Mountain God
comes near human dwellings

522
00:13:27,240 --> 00:13:29,540
is when someone kidnaps its child!

523
00:13:29,960 --> 00:13:32,880
So someone brought its child to the capital?!

524
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:35,790
We must placate the Mountain God!

525
00:13:35,790 --> 00:13:38,260
Find a small white boar!

526
00:13:38,260 --> 00:13:43,090
If we can't send the white boar back
to the mountain, the capital will be destroyed!

527
00:13:49,270 --> 00:13:51,640
Help me! Help!

528
00:13:54,360 --> 00:13:56,480
It's eating houses and people alike!

529
00:13:56,480 --> 00:13:57,980
Dad!

530
00:13:57,980 --> 00:13:59,320
What a nightmare!

531
00:14:09,910 --> 00:14:11,830
There you are! I've been looking for you!

532
00:14:12,160 --> 00:14:14,290
You're the boar kidnapper!

533
00:14:14,290 --> 00:14:16,250
But you took it from me!

534
00:14:16,790 --> 00:14:19,670
Take it back to the mountain already!

535
00:14:19,670 --> 00:14:24,390
That monster will come straight for us
if it catches a whiff of the little one!

536
00:14:24,390 --> 00:14:25,010
What?!

537
00:14:25,430 --> 00:14:28,810
We had no idea this would happen!

538
00:14:28,810 --> 00:14:34,440
The Mountain God swallowed my two partners
because their clothes smelled like that boar!

539
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:36,610
And your friend Otsuru, too!

540
00:14:37,650 --> 00:14:38,730
Why her?!

541
00:14:38,730 --> 00:14:41,780
To get the white boar back from you,

542
00:14:41,780 --> 00:14:45,110
we took her hostage and were
headed down the mountain.

543
00:14:47,320 --> 00:14:50,830
It ate everyone! It's all your fault!

544
00:14:58,380 --> 00:14:59,130
Kin!

545
00:15:08,140 --> 00:15:13,640
That monster will come straight for us
if it catches a whiff of the little one!

546
00:15:17,730 --> 00:15:19,150
Get out of my way!

547
00:15:21,610 --> 00:15:22,900
It's coming this way!

548
00:15:36,460 --> 00:15:39,170
What? Kin stole something again?!

549
00:15:39,170 --> 00:15:42,300
I'm sorry! Let me pay for it!

550
00:15:46,220 --> 00:15:48,430
Kin, you need to get a job.

551
00:15:48,430 --> 00:15:50,390
The yakuza are always after you!

552
00:15:50,720 --> 00:15:52,220
You'll get killed!

553
00:15:52,220 --> 00:15:53,220
Who cares?!

554
00:15:53,220 --> 00:15:55,600
No one will mourn my death!

555
00:16:00,480 --> 00:16:02,730
Ouch! Don't hit me with a rock!

556
00:16:04,030 --> 00:16:07,780
Give me back Tsuru!

557
00:16:45,820 --> 00:16:47,280
Stop it, kid!

558
00:16:47,280 --> 00:16:50,910
If you harm the Mountain God,
Wano will be destroyed!

559
00:16:50,910 --> 00:16:53,780
I'm gonna cut that belly open!

560
00:16:54,410 --> 00:16:56,410
You call yourself a god?!

561
00:16:56,410 --> 00:16:59,290
Give me back Tsuru!

562
00:17:05,800 --> 00:17:06,710
Kin!

563
00:17:17,980 --> 00:17:20,190
Kin! Stop it!

564
00:17:21,400 --> 00:17:23,860
He sure has guts.

565
00:17:40,620 --> 00:17:43,830
If Tsuru dies because of me...

566
00:17:49,210 --> 00:17:51,130
then I wanna die, too!

567
00:18:17,280 --> 00:18:21,790
Is this what you're looking for, boar?!

568
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:25,290
It's that accursed boy, Kozuki Oden!

569
00:18:25,710 --> 00:18:27,290
Not him again!

570
00:18:27,290 --> 00:18:30,010
He must've caused all of this!

571
00:18:30,460 --> 00:18:32,170
This boar will make a good hot pot.

572
00:18:34,300 --> 00:18:36,600
How could you do this to us?!

573
00:18:36,600 --> 00:18:38,220
Bring my mother back!

574
00:18:39,390 --> 00:18:40,180
No...

575
00:18:40,720 --> 00:18:42,060
It's a misunderstanding...

576
00:18:42,060 --> 00:18:43,730
Give my daughter back!

577
00:18:44,310 --> 00:18:47,810
I'm the one who brought that white boar here!

578
00:18:48,230 --> 00:18:52,650
It's my fault the capital is in this mess!

579
00:19:05,290 --> 00:19:07,540
Oden Two-Sword Style!

580
00:19:38,280 --> 00:19:38,320
Hal

581
00:19:38,280 --> 00:19:38,370
Hal

582
00:19:38,370 --> 00:19:38,620
Halcyon

583
00:19:38,450 --> 00:19:38,530
Fall

584
00:19:38,530 --> 00:19:38,620
Falls

585
00:19:41,620 --> 00:19:43,580
Halcyon Falls!

586
00:19:43,580 --> 00:19:45,080
– What?!
– What?!

587
00:19:51,290 --> 00:19:53,050
He sure is something.

588
00:19:53,630 --> 00:19:55,010
Let's go home.

589
00:20:01,760 --> 00:20:05,100
They said the people and houses
that got swallowed

590
00:20:05,100 --> 00:20:09,310
could have formed a new town
in the boar's stomach.

591
00:20:10,060 --> 00:20:16,650
It destroyed a quarter of the capital,
but miraculously, no one died.

592
00:20:17,070 --> 00:20:18,780
Kin!

593
00:20:25,830 --> 00:20:28,370
Oden was so cool...

594
00:20:28,370 --> 00:20:31,000
...so cool that I almost screamed!

595
00:20:31,630 --> 00:20:34,500
I can't even tell him how grateful I am!

596
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:37,720
It's all his fault! He's evil!

597
00:20:37,720 --> 00:20:39,890
Everyone, listen up!

598
00:20:39,890 --> 00:20:41,600
What really happened was–

599
00:20:43,930 --> 00:20:46,020
Perish the thought!

600
00:20:46,600 --> 00:20:48,520
Lord Oden!

601
00:20:48,520 --> 00:20:49,520
Notice
of
Disownment

602
00:20:49,520 --> 00:20:53,440
I am sorry to give this to you
on such an auspicious occasion.

